We recommended that Management :
a.	Direct all JO employees to comply strictly with Section 1 to 5 of CSC Memorandum Circular No. 01, s. 2017;
b.	Strictly require all JO employees assigned in the SP Office to time in and out using the biometrics machine and to report for work in the Office from eight o’clock to twelve o’clock in the morning and from one o’clock to five o’clock in the afternoon from Monday to Friday, in order to ensure that the amount of wages paid by the government is based on the services they rendered and to prevent any doubts of ghost employee;
c.	Limit the hiring of JOs to three (3) per SP Member as early as possible and refrain from hiring their immediate members of the family as JO;
d.	Instruct the SDO to stop immediately the practice of releasing the wages to person other than the claimant listed in the payroll based on an authorization letter without valid reason except in very exceptional cases where the concerned claimant cannot come in person under the power of attorney.

We recommended that the management observe strictly the PCW, DILG, DBM and NEDA Joint Circular No. 2013-01and COA Circular No. 2014-01 on the following GAD issues:
1.	That the SangguniangPanglungsod formulate and pass the LGU GAD    Code to be included in the GAD Plan and Budget (GPB);
2.	Establish and maintain a Violence against Women (VAW) desk to be   included in the GPB;
3.	Stop the incurrence of GPB expenses for the Family Day Activity which are not client-focused; and
4.	Prepare and submit the GAD Accomplishment Report to the COA   Audit Team on a timely basis.

Cause the formation of the Local Waste Management Board  that shall prepare the City’s Solid Waste Management Plans consistent with the national solid waste management framework;
Cause the creation of a City Local Environment and Natural Resources Office (CLENRO) and the hiring of an officer who will ensure that proper solid waste management is implemented and monitored, and

Apply/ obtain an  Environmental Compliance Certificate (ECC) from the DENR for the operation of the dumpsite in Barangay Himaya.

Locate the supporting records/ disbursement vouchers of the properties to identify the  person/s who were responsible/ accountable for the loss of these properties; 
Request the assistance of present DepEd officers to locate the addresses of end-users or those who are responsible/ liable for the loss of these properties;
Require the Division Superintendent the submission to the COA Director, a request for relief from property accountability, citing strong justification why she should not be held accountable or liable for the loss of the above-listed properties; and 
Strictly observe existing regulations on property management, such as the issuance of the ARE to requisitioners or end-users, proper turnover to newly  assumed personnel and during issuance of personnel clearances, regular conduct of 
physical inventory taking and RPCPPE submission.

